name: CarbonMarketplace

methods.name: register_business
methods.desc: Company registers to buy credits. Starts pending.

methods.name: list_credit
methods.desc:
NGO lists a carbon credit NFT for sale.
expiry_timestamp: pass in the value from get_credit_expiry() Contract stores it so buy_credit() can enforce it on-chain.
Call as atomic group:     [0] AssetTransfer — seller sends NFT to contract     [1] AppCall       — this method
Box layout (total 96 bytes): asset_id(8) | seller(32) | price(8) | co2(8) | vintage(8)  | min_qty(8) | timestamp(8) | expiry(8) | active(8)

methods.name: buy_credit
methods.desc:
Verified business buys a listed carbon credit.
✅ Checks: - Buyer is a verified business - Listing is active - Credit has NOT expired (enforced on-chain by blockchain time) - Payment matches listing price
Call as atomic group:     [0] Payment  — buyer pays exact price to contract     [1] AppCall  — this method

methods.name: cancel_listing
methods.desc: Seller cancels listing and gets NFT back.

methods.name: get_listing
methods.desc:
Get full listing details.
Returns: (seller, price_microalgo, co2_tonnes, min_purchase_qty, expiry_timestamp, active)
Frontend: use expiry_timestamp to show countdown timer If current time > expiry_timestamp → show EXPIRED badge

methods.name: is_listing_expired
methods.desc:
Check if a listing has expired.
Returns True if expired, False if still valid.

desc:
Contract 2 — Carbon Credit Marketplace (with Expiry Enforcement)

    New expiry features:
    - Expiry timestamp stored in every listing
    - buy_credit() rejects expired credits on-chain
    - get_listing() returns expiry so frontend can show countdown
    - Expired listings can be cleaned up by anyone
